If you don't know about [Mavo](https://mavo.io/), it mainly helps you turn your static HTML into reactive web applications without a single line of programming code and no server backend. The blog area of my website, for example, is made of Mavo's *magic*. 

Now let's talk about how to use Disqus inside Mavo so you can have a comment section in your blog as well!

As you can read in the tweet bellow, a plugin is on the way to make it super easy, until then you can follow the instructions in this post.
<blockquote class="twitter-tweet" data-conversation="none" data-lang="pt"><p lang="en" dir="ltr">I&#39;m so excited you got <a href="https://twitter.com/disqus?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">@disqus</a> working with Mavo! w00t!! I&#39;ve been wondering how to do it for a while!<br>Iâ€™ll make a plugin or something to make it easier so that people don&#39;t have to write any JS.</p>&mdash; Lea Verou (@LeaVerou) <a href="https://twitter.com/LeaVerou/status/932752118070546432?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">20 de novembro de 2017</a></blockquote>
<script async src="https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8"></script>

### Set up you Disqus

1. Log into your Disqus account [here](https://disqus.com) and then click in "Get Started".

2. Select "I want to install Disqus on my site" option.
![disqus screenshot][sd-logo]

3. Fill in the fields with your website's data and then save by clicking on "Create website".

4. Select a plan, you can use "Basic" to start with.

5. In the "What platform is your site on?" step, scroll down and select "Universal Code" option.
![disqus screenshot 2](https://github.com/laistomazz/laistomaz/blob/master/content/2017/11/02.png)

6. Copy the code inside box number 1.
![disqus screenshot 3](https://github.com/laistomazz/laistomaz/blob/master/content/2017/11/03.png)

### Edit Disqus's code

1 - Remove Javascript comments
```html
<div id="disqus_thread"></div>
<script>

/**
*  RECOMMENDED CONFIGURATION VARIABLES: EDIT AND UNCOMMENT THE SECTION BELOW TO INSERT DYNAMIC VALUES FROM YOUR PLATFORM OR CMS.
*  LEARN WHY DEFINING THESE VARIABLES IS IMPORTANT: https://disqus.com/admin/universalcode/#configuration-variables*/
/*
var disqus_config = function () {
this.page.url = PAGE_URL;  // Replace PAGE_URL with your page's canonical URL variable
this.page.identifier = PAGE_IDENTIFIER; // Replace PAGE_IDENTIFIER with your page's unique identifier variable
};
*/
(function() { // DON'T EDIT BELOW THIS LINE
var d = document, s = d.createElement('script');
s.src = 'https://wefwef.disqus.com/embed.js';
s.setAttribute('data-timestamp', +new Date());
(d.head || d.body).appendChild(s);
})();
</script>
<noscript>Please enable JavaScript to view the <a href="https://disqus.com/?ref_noscript">comments powered by Disqus.</a></noscript>
```

It will look like this:

```html
<div id="disqus_thread"></div>
<script>

var disqus_config = function () {
this.page.url = PAGE_URL;  // Replace PAGE_URL with your page's canonical URL variable
this.page.identifier = PAGE_IDENTIFIER; // Replace PAGE_IDENTIFIER with your page's unique identifier variable
};

(function() { // DON'T EDIT BELOW THIS LINE
var d = document, s = d.createElement('script');
s.src = 'https://wefwef.disqus.com/embed.js';
s.setAttribute('data-timestamp', +new Date());
(d.head || d.body).appendChild(s);
})();
</script>
<noscript>Please enable JavaScript to view the <a href="https://disqus.com/?ref_noscript">comments powered by Disqus.</a></noscript>
```

2 - Replace **PAGE_URL** and **PAGE_IDENTIFIER**

**PAGE_URL** will become `Mavo.Functions.url()`.

**PAGE_IDENTIFIER** is a little bit more complicated. Here you need pass a value that differentiates one page from another.

If you look in the url of this page, you can see something like `?post=the-title-of-this-post`. This means I use `post` as the parameter to pass the `id` of my post. It's unique. So in my case:
**PAGE_IDENTIFIER** will become `Mavo.Functions.url('post')`.

Now let's use them in our code:

```html
<div id="disqus_thread"></div>
<script>

var disqus_config = function () {
this.page.url = Mavo.Functions.url();  // Replace PAGE_URL with your page's canonical URL variable
this.page.identifier = Mavo.Functions.url('post'); // Replace PAGE_IDENTIFIER with your page's unique identifier variable
};

(function() { // DON'T EDIT BELOW THIS LINE
var d = document, s = d.createElement('script');
s.src = 'https://wefwef.disqus.com/embed.js';
s.setAttribute('data-timestamp', +new Date());
(d.head || d.body).appendChild(s);
})();
</script>
<noscript>Please enable JavaScript to view the <a href="https://disqus.com/?ref_noscript">comments powered by Disqus.</a></noscript>
```

3 - Finally paste it into your Mavo's code, where you want the comment section to show.

***

I hope this post was useful to you, if you have any questions or suggestions, please comment bellow.

Once Mavo's plugin for Disqus is available, I will edit this post and link it here.

Thanks for reading!

